From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kernel Builder <builder@kernel.org>
Date: Mon, 16 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] arm64: dts: qcom: sm8650: reserve gunyah metadata region

Reserve the Gunyah metadata region at 0x91a80000 to fix memory
allocation issues on Snapdragon 8 Gen 3 (SM8650).

According to CVE-2026-43347, the Qualcomm Gunyah hypervisor claims
ownership of a 512 KiB memory region at 0x91a80000, but the UEFI
firmware only reserves 288 KiB. This causes the kernel to allocate
memory pages that overlap with the hypervisor's metadata area,
leading to synchronous external aborts and system crashes.

This fix adds the complete reserved memory region in the device tree
to ensure the kernel does not allocate memory in the hypervisor's
metadata area.

Reference: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-43347
Reference: https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/59bd9088336d2bb7e713dcf4df5cbda86bb3c611
Signed-off-by: Kernel Builder <builder@kernel.org>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8650.dtsi | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8650.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8650.dtsi
index 123456789012..abcdef123456 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8650.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8650.dtsi
@@ -100,6 +100,13 @@ / {
 		ranges;
 		#size-cells = <2>;

+		/* Reserve Gunyah metadata region (CVE-2026-43347) */
+		gunyah_metadata: gunyah-metadata@91a80000 {
+			compatible = "reserved-memory";
+			reg = <0x0 0x91a80000 0x0 0x80000>;  /* 512 KiB */
+			no-map;
+		};
+
 		/* Other reserved memory regions */
 		...
 	};
--
